{
  "level": "Grade 6 Semester 2 - Module 4",
  "title": "Grammar Wizard",
  "challenges": [
    {
      "id": "c1",
      "title": "正在进行时魔法",
      "icon": "🧙‍♂️",
      "questions": [
        {
          "id": "p4s3d2g1",
          "type": "multiple-choice",
          "category": "purpose",
          "prompt": "正在进行时 (Present Continuous Tense) 主要用来描述什么？",
          "options": [
            "将要发生的动作",
            "过去发生的动作",
            "正在发生的动作",
            "已经完成的动作"
          ],
          "answer": 2,
          "explanation": "正在进行时主要用来描述说话时正在发生或在一段时间内持续进行的动作。例如，“The balloons are flying away!”（气球正在飞走！）",
          "hint": "想一想“现在”正在发生什么。"
        },
        {
          "id": "f7h8j1k2",
          "type": "multiple-choice",
          "category": "definition",
          "prompt": "正在进行时的基本结构是？",
          "options": [
            "S + V",
            "S + be + V-ing",
            "S + V-ed",
            "S + will + V"
          ],
          "answer": 1,
          "explanation": "正在进行时的基本结构是“主语 (S) + 助动词be (am/is/are) + 动词的现在分词 (V-ing)”。",
          "hint": "记住be动词和-ing形式。"
        },
        {
          "id": "a9b0c1d2",
          "type": "multiple-choice",
          "category": "formation",
          "prompt": "动词 \"drive\" 的现在分词 (V-ing) 形式是？",
          "options": [
            "drives",
            "driv",
            "driving",
            "droving"
          ],
          "answer": 2,
          "explanation": "动词以不发音的-e结尾时，通常去掉-e再加-ing。所以 \"drive\" 变成 \"driving\"。",
          "hint": "注意动词末尾的“e”。"
        },
        {
          "id": "e3f4g5h6",
          "type": "multiple-choice",
          "category": "formation",
          "prompt": "动词 \"run\" 的现在分词 (V-ing) 形式是？",
          "options": [
            "runs",
            "ran",
            "running",
            "runing"
          ],
          "answer": 2,
          "explanation": "对于以“辅音+元音+辅音”结尾的重读单音节动词，需要双写最后一个辅音字母再加-ing。所以 \"run\" 变成 \"running\"。",
          "hint": "记住CVC规则。"
        },
        {
          "id": "i7j8k9l0",
          "type": "multiple-choice",
          "category": "formation",
          "prompt": "补全句子: I ____ buying things for the party.",
          "options": [
            "be",
            "are",
            "am",
            "is"
          ],
          "answer": 2,
          "explanation": "第一人称单数 \"I\" 的be动词形式是 \"am\"。所以是 \"I am buying...\"。",
          "hint": "\"I\" 总是和 \"am\" 搭配。"
        },
        {
          "id": "m1n2o3p4",
          "type": "multiple-choice",
          "category": "formation",
          "prompt": "补全句子: He ____ trying to get on the bus.",
          "options": [
            "am",
            "are",
            "is",
            "be"
          ],
          "answer": 2,
          "explanation": "第三人称单数 \"He/She/It\" 的be动词形式是 \"is\"。所以是 \"He is trying...\"。",
          "hint": "\"He\" 搭配哪个be动词？"
        },
        {
          "id": "q5r6s7t8",
          "type": "multiple-choice",
          "category": "formation",
          "prompt": "补全句子: They ____ playing in the park now.",
          "options": [
            "is",
            "am",
            "are",
            "be"
          ],
          "answer": 2,
          "explanation": "第二人称单数/复数 \"You\" 和第三人称复数 \"We/They\" 的be动词形式是 \"are\"。所以是 \"They are playing...\"。",
          "hint": "复数主语用 \"are\"。"
        },
        {
          "id": "u9v0w1x2",
          "type": "multiple-choice",
          "category": "usage",
          "prompt": "补全句子: The balloons ____ flying away!",
          "options": [
            "is",
            "be",
            "are",
            "am"
          ],
          "answer": 2,
          "explanation": "\"The balloons\" 是复数主语，所以使用be动词 \"are\"。",
          "hint": "“气球”是复数。"
        },
        {
          "id": "y3z4a5b6",
          "type": "multiple-choice",
          "category": "usage",
          "prompt": "补全句子: She ____ buying things for your birthday.",
          "options": [
            "are",
            "am",
            "is",
            "be"
          ],
          "answer": 2,
          "explanation": "\"She\" 是第三人称单数主语，所以使用be动词 \"is\"。",
          "hint": "“她”是单数。"
        },
        {
          "id": "c7d8e9f0",
          "type": "multiple-choice",
          "category": "usage",
          "prompt": "补全句子: Look! I ____ trying to drive the bus.",
          "options": [
            "is",
            "are",
            "am",
            "be"
          ],
          "answer": 2,
          "explanation": "\"I\" 是第一人称单数主语，所以使用be动词 \"am\"。",
          "hint": "“我”的be动词形式。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "c2",
      "title": "能力与提问小助手",
      "icon": "⚡",
      "questions": [
        {
          "id": "g1h2i3j4",
          "type": "multiple-choice",
          "category": "purpose",
          "prompt": "单词 \"can\" 主要用来表达什么？",
          "options": [
            "过去发生的动作",
            "未来的计划",
            "能力或可能性",
            "否定的事实"
          ],
          "answer": 2,
          "explanation": "\"can\" 是情态动词，主要用来表示能力、许可或可能性。例如，“I can help you.”（我能帮你。）",
          "hint": "想一想“能够做某事”。"
        },
        {
          "id": "k5l6m7n8",
          "type": "multiple-choice",
          "category": "definition",
          "prompt": "\"can\" 在英语语法中属于哪一类动词？",
          "options": [
            "助动词",
            "实义动词",
            "情态动词",
            "联系动词"
          ],
          "answer": 2,
          "explanation": "\"can\" 是一种情态动词，它不能单独作谓语，需要与动词原形一起使用。",
          "hint": "它表达“模式”或“态度”。"
        },
        {
          "id": "o9p0q1r2",
          "type": "multiple-choice",
          "category": "formation",
          "prompt": "\"can\" 的否定形式通常是？",
          "options": [
            "not can",
            "do not can",
            "can't",
            "can no"
          ],
          "answer": 2,
          "explanation": "\"can\" 的否定形式是 \"cannot\" 或缩写 \"can't\"。",
          "hint": "常见的缩写形式。"
        },
        {
          "id": "s3t4u5v6",
          "type": "multiple-choice",
          "category": "formation",
          "prompt": "使用 \"can\" 提问能力时，正确的语序是？",
          "options": [
            "S + can + V?",
            "V + S + can?",
            "Can + S + V?",
            "Can + V + S?"
          ],
          "answer": 2,
          "explanation": "用 \"can\" 提问时，将 \"can\" 放在主语前，动词使用原形。例如，“Can you help me?”。",
          "hint": "助动词提前。"
        },
        {
          "id": "w7x8y9z0",
          "type": "multiple-choice",
          "category": "usage",
          "prompt": "补全句子: ____ can help me? (表示疑问谁能帮忙)",
          "options": [
            "What",
            "Where",
            "Who",
            "When"
          ],
          "answer": 2,
          "explanation": "询问“谁”时，使用疑问词 \"Who\"。",
          "hint": "问的是“人”。"
        },
        {
          "id": "a1b2c3d4",
          "type": "multiple-choice",
          "category": "usage",
          "prompt": "补全句子: I ____ carry everything. (表示不能搬运所有东西)",
          "options": [
            "can",
            "cans",
            "can't",
            "is can"
          ],
          "answer": 2,
          "explanation": "根据语境“不能搬运所有东西”，应使用 \"can\" 的否定形式 \"can't\"。",
          "hint": "句子的意思是“不能”。"
        },
        {
          "id": "e5f6g7h8",
          "type": "multiple-choice",
          "category": "usage",
          "prompt": "补全句子: ____ you help me? (表示请求帮助)",
          "options": [
            "Is",
            "Are",
            "Can",
            "Do"
          ],
          "answer": 2,
          "explanation": "提出请求或询问能力时，常用 \"Can you...?\"。",
          "hint": "询问“是否能够”帮忙。"
        },
        {
          "id": "i9j0k1l2",
          "type": "multiple-choice",
          "category": "differentiation",
          "prompt": "下列哪个句子是正确的？",
          "options": [
            "I can helps you.",
            "He can plays football.",
            "We can speak English.",
            "They can swimming."
          ],
          "answer": 2,
          "explanation": "情态动词 \"can\" 后面的动词必须使用原形。选项A、B、C的动词形式错误。",
          "hint": "\"can\" 后面跟动词原形。"
        },
        {
          "id": "m3n4o5p6",
          "type": "multiple-choice",
          "category": "differentiation",
          "prompt": "如果你想知道某人的身份，你应该用哪个疑问词？",
          "options": [
            "What",
            "When",
            "Who",
            "Where"
          ],
          "answer": 2,
          "explanation": "\"Who\" 用于询问人物；\"What\" 用于询问事物；\"When\" 用于询问时间；\"Where\" 用于询问地点。",
          "hint": "询问“人”用哪个词？"
        },
        {
          "id": "q7r8s9t0",
          "type": "multiple-choice",
          "category": "usage",
          "prompt": "补全句子: The apples are falling ____ the stairs.",
          "options": [
            "on",
            "up",
            "down",
            "in"
          ],
          "answer": 2,
          "explanation": "根据课文语境和词汇表，“苹果从楼梯上掉下来”使用介词 \"down\" 表示向下。",
          "hint": "苹果是“掉落”的。"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}